    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "<!-- Before reporting: search existing issues and check the FAQ. -->\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`: NVIM v0.5.0-418-g87d892afa\r\n- `vim -u DEFAULTS` (version: ) behaves differently? Yes - VIM - Vi IMproved 8.2 (2019 Dec 12, compiled Mar 23 2020 08:34:29) Included patches: 1-430\r\n- Operating system/version: Linux 5.3.0-40-generic #32~18.04.1-Ubuntu SMP Mon Feb 3 14:05:59 UTC 2020 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n\r\nUse the following init.vim:\r\n```vim\r\nautocmd BufRead * echom \"BufRead\"\r\nautocmd BufReadPost * echom \"BufReadPost\"\r\nautocmd BufNewFile * echom \"BufNewFile\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim -u init.vim\r\n:e init.vim\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\nNothing is printed.\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n`BufRead` and `BufReadPost` are printed.",
