            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "This is because `F` is included in default of `shortmess` in neovim, it is not a bug. You should see the message if you do the following:\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim -u init.vim -c \"set shm-=F\"\r\n:e init.vim\r\n```\r\n\r\nOr you can change the `echom \"BufRead\"` to `let g:BufRead = 1` to see that `autocmd` is firing.",
